![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/c73e6254-d81b-4089-823d-31b30f1f9c9e/Screenshot_20240419_174101.jpg)

Naomi cuts a promo promising her friendship with Bayley won’t be in trouble after this match… Uh oh.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/8e5c1d23-6554-4864-9a42-51b89f2d1521/received_979936290189675.jpeg)

*   ## _STREET PROFITS DEF. NEW CATCH REPUBLIC, LEGADO DEL FANTASMA AND AUTHORS OF PAIN TO BECOME NUMBER 1 CONTENDERS FOR THE WWE TAG TEAM CHAMPIONSHIPS_
    

Freaking excellent match. Sick spot where NCR does double moonsaults to the outside while Montez hops the turnbuckle. Go seek this out.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/58e18192-901b-428e-9a72-2206711a2eec/Screenshot_20240419_180929.jpg)

Paul Heyman tells Solo Sikoa that Solo has been making decisions that aren’t yet his to make. They will be one day but not yet. Solo doesn’t want to hear any of it.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/0f784fd1-3b26-4d98-b728-d64e27a3350a/20240419_181248.jpg)

Solo Sikoa snatches the mic out of Heyman's hands and the crowd is screaming for Roman Reigns. Solo is not pleased.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/a3b3ed27-07a2-482d-905f-fb9c774bff6e/20240419_181528.jpg)

Tama Tonga brings out a bloody Kevin Owens! This is nasty

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/d3f60535-474a-479a-845e-b5aff4275c75/20240419_181505.jpg)

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/f37dafc4-aebd-4906-8f5f-36c2789fd693/20240419_182300.jpg)

It turns out Tama Tonga tried to kill KO before they came out. Aldis told Heyman to keep The Bloodline in control because Tama Tonga’s actions would have repercussions for the WWE Draft.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/c45d037a-690f-4cc2-8957-a9d2087f5810/20240419_191119.jpg)

*   ## **_Santos Escobar (w/ Elektra Lopez) def. Carlito Colon (w/ Zelina Vega)_**
    

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/0f081a20-8bdd-410e-99c4-cfa303ffcdce/20240419_191134.jpg)

Kayla Braxton interviewed Damage CTRL from a skybox. Kai scolded Braxton for naming Sky as the FORMER Women's Champion and said that DamageCTRL was still the most dominant faction in WWE.

This led to Bianca Belair & Jade Cargill and joining them in the skybox next to them in the crowd. This led directly to the main event of the night.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5940fe6a-ac00-4144-b0be-49a3b142efcf/20240419_191703.jpg)

*   ## **_WWE Women's Championship Match: Bayley (c) def. Naomi via Disqualification._**
    

Tiffany Stratton attacked Bayley from behind on the outside, ending the match via disqualification. Stratton attacked Naomi & Bayley before getting them back in the ring and hitting them with the PME (Prettiest Moonsault Ever). Stratton stood tall to end the broadcast.